180Ôćĺ\section{The Koide Formula as Energy Balance}
181Ôćĺ\label{sec:koide_algebra}
182Ôćĺ%======================================================================
183Ôćĺ
184Ôćĺ\subsection{Charges, not masses}
185Ôćĺ
186ÔćĺThe fundamental variable is the signed mass charge $\zch = z_0 + z_i 
187Ôćĺ\in \mathbb{R}$, with the physical mass $m = \zch^2 \geq 0$.
188Ôćĺ
189Ôćĺ\subsection{Derivation of $Q = 2/3$}
190Ôćĺ
191ÔćĺFor three charges $\zch_k = z_0 + z_k$ with $z_0$ the mean 
192Ôćĺ($\sum z_k = 0$):
193Ôćĺ\begin{equation}
194ÔćĺQ = \frac{\sum \zch_k^2}{(\sum \zch_k)^2} 
195Ôćĺ= \frac{3z_0^2 + \sum z_k^2}{9z_0^2}
196Ôćĺ= \frac{1}{3} + \frac{\langle z_k^2\rangle}{3z_0^2}\,.
197Ôćĺ\end{equation}
198ÔćĺTherefore:
199Ôćĺ\begin{equation}
200Ôćĺ\boxed{Q = \frac{2}{3} \quad\Longleftrightarrow\quad 
201Ôćĺ\langle z_k^2\rangle = z_0^2\,.}
202Ôćĺ\end{equation}
203Ôćĺ
204ÔćĺThe two conditions are:
205Ôćĺ\begin{enumerate}
206Ôćĺ\item \textbf{Zero-sum perturbations:} $z_1 + z_2 + z_3 = 0$ 
207Ôćĺ(definition of $z_0$ as the mean charge).
208Ôćĺ\item \textbf{Energy balance:} The mean energy of the perturbations 
209Ôćĺequals the energy of the unperturbed charge: 
210Ôćĺ$\langle z_k^2\rangle = z_0^2$.
211Ôćĺ\end{enumerate}
212Ôćĺ
213ÔćĺCondition~2 is the physics. It says the splitting scale matches the
214Ôćĺbase scale---the coefficient of variation equals unity:
215Ôćĺ$\sigma(\zch)/\bar{\zch} = 1$.
216Ôćĺ(Dimensionally, $\zch$ has units $\MeV^{1/2}$, so
217Ôćĺ$z_0^2$ has units MeV---a mass scale, not an energy density.
218ÔćĺThe ``energy balance'' terminology is metaphorical.) This is neither perturbative 
219Ôćĺ($\sigma \ll \bar{\zch}$, giving $Q \to 1/3$, all equal) nor 
220Ôćĺdominant ($\sigma \gg \bar{\zch}$, giving $Q \to 1$, one mass 
221Ôćĺdominates). The Koide value $2/3$ is the equipartition point.
222Ôćĺ
223Ôćĺ\subsection{Why one mass can vanish}
224Ôćĺ
225ÔćĺIf $\langle z_k^2\rangle = z_0^2$, a perturbation $z_k$ can reach 
226Ôćĺ$|z_k| \sim z_0$, making $\zch_k = z_0 + z_k \approx 0$. A vanishing 
227Ôćĺmass is the \emph{natural extreme} of energy balance, not fine-tuning.
228Ôćĺ
